The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Afghan blast
                                                                                                               Afghan blast
                            
	Kandahar, Aug. 6 (Reuters): A roadside bomb struck a tractor carrying revellers to a wedding in southern Afghanistan, killing 21 civilians.        
	Assadullah Sherzad, police chief of Helmand province, said by telephone that the dead included women and children heading to a wedding in a trailer hauled by a tractor.                                                                                                                                                                                      
